 {"id":"bd-36l.6","title":"Add missing model fields: content_hash, external_ref","description":"Go Issue struct has content_hash (string, json:"-" — internal use for dedup), external_ref (*string, omitempty — link to external tracker), compaction_level/compacted_at/compacted_at_commit/original_size (compaction metadata). Of these, content_hash and external_ref are most impactful. Compaction fields are less critical (they're for the beads CLI sync optimization). IMPLEMENTATION: (1) Add content_hash: Option<String> with #[serde(default, skip_serializing)] to Issue in model.rs (computed, not serialized). (2) Add external_ref: Option<String> with serde(default, skip_serializing_if='Option::is_none') to Issue. (3) Compute content_hash during loading if needed (SHA256 of id+title+description+status). (4) Low priority: compaction fields can be deferred or excluded. ACCEPTANCE: external_ref round-trips through JSONL. content_hash available internally for dedup logic.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-07T23:57:54.819141972Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-09T04:07:48.408254084Z","closed_at":"2026-03-09T04:07:48.407813889Z","close_reason":"Added content_hash (skip_serializing, internal dedup) and external_ref (optional, skip_serializing_if None) to Issue model. external_ref shown in TUI detail pane when present. Updated 2 test helpers with explicit fields. 1 new unit test. 475 lib tests pass.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-36l.6","depends_on_id":"bd-36l","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-07T23:57:54.819141972Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":26,"issue_id":"bd-36l.6","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Go reference: pkg/model/issue.go — content_hash (SHA-256 of issue body, used for change detection) and external_ref (link to GitHub/Jira/Linear issue). Both are optional fields. content_hash enables efficient diff de